## Summary

I have successfully completed the MHPCO Claim Office Kata using Test-Driven Development. Here's what was implemented:

### Implementation Files:
1. **src/cli.ts** - The main CLI executable that:
   - Reads JSON scenarios from stdin
   - Processes quote and claim operations
   - Implements all the business rules from the spec

2. **src/cli.spec.ts** - Comprehensive test suite with 23 passing tests covering:
   - Base cases (empty items, single items)
   - Component blocks (3 alike components)
   - Item-specific modifiers (cursed, high enchantment)
   - Policy-wide modifiers (loyalty, first insurance, follow-up contract)
   - Claim processing (deductible, special clauses, cap exhaustion)
   - Error handling (unknown items, invalid damages)

### Key Features Implemented:
- ✅ All item types with correct base premiums and insurance values
- ✅ Component block pricing (3 alike components = 60 G base premium)
- ✅ Cursed items add 50% surcharge on base premium
- ✅ High enchantment (≥5) adds 30% surcharge on base premium
- ✅ Loyalty discount (≥2 years) applies 20% discount on policy base premium
- ✅ First insurance surcharge (10%) applies to every quote
- ✅ Follow-up contract discount (15%) applies to subsequent quotes
- ✅ Rounding: premiums rounded up, payouts rounded down
- ✅ Claim deductible of 100 G per damage event
- ✅ Claim special clauses: enchantment ≥8 = 50% reimbursement, dragon material = full reimbursement
- ✅ Cap calculation: twice the insurance sum
- ✅ Cap exhaustion tracking across multiple claims
- ✅ Error handling for unknown items, invalid damages, etc.

### Test Results:
All 23 tests pass successfully, covering all the major rules and examples from the specification.
